library("microbenchmark")
library(glue)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(ggdark)
options(repr.plot.width=18, repr.plot.height=7)
# function to calculate reduction
calcpecentage <- function(micro){
  v <- aggregate(time ~ expr, micro, mean)
  i <- 1
  j <- 2
  if(v$time[i] < v$time[j]){
    i <- 2
    j <- 1
  }
  reduction <- ((v$time[i] - v$time[j])*100)/v$time[i]
  reduction <- reduction |> round(digits = 2)
  return(glue("{reduction} % reduction using {v$expr[j]}"))
}
start_date <- "2017-01-01"
end_date <- "2019-12-31"
f1<-function(d2, d1){
  n_weeks <-  floor(as.numeric(difftime(d2, d1, units="weeks")))
  # print(glue("Result 1: {n_weeks_in_scaling_period}"))
}
f2<-function(d2, d1){
  n_weeks <- floor(as.numeric(difftime(as.Date(d2), as.Date(d1), units = "weeks")))
  # print(glue("Result 2: {n_weeks_in_scaling_period}"))
}
m1<-microbenchmark(
  Nocasting = f1(end_date, start_date),
  Casting = f2(end_date, start_date),
  times = 800
)
print(m1)
## Unit: microseconds
##       expr     min      lq     mean   median      uq       max neval
##  Nocasting 285.501 314.551 415.4471 332.0015 366.001 35017.301   800
##    Casting 113.201 125.901 162.5035 134.5510 152.101  5765.301   800
m1 |> boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison casting dates',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m1)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.2, cex.lab = 1.2, cex.axis = 1.2)

# + ggdark::dark_mode()
# m1$time
ggplot(data = m1, aes(x = time, y = expr)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  # geom_line() +
  labs(y = "Function", x = "Execution Time (ms)",
       title = "Microbenchmark Results: Execution Time by Function") + ggdark::dark_mode()

# Base code vs dplyr

# Example data frame with points scored by players
set.seed(1)
mydemo <- data.frame(
  team = rep(c('A', 'B'), each = 4000),
  points =sample(1:100, 8000, replace = TRUE)
)
print(head(mydemo))
##   team points
## 1    A     68
## 2    A     39
## 3    A      1
## 4    A     34
## 5    A     87
## 6    A     43
base_r_time <- function(mydemo){
  x <- aggregate(mydemo$points, list(mydemo$team), FUN = mean)
  # print(x)
}
dplyr_time <- function(mydemo){
  x <- mydemo %>% group_by(team) %>% summarise_at(vars(points), list(name = mean))
  # print(x)
}
m2 <- microbenchmark(
  base = base_r_time(mydemo),
  dplyr = dplyr_time(mydemo),
  times = 30
)
print(m2)
## Unit: milliseconds
##   expr      min       lq     mean   median       uq       max neval
##   base 2.792101 3.041901 3.400845 3.170201 3.483201  5.761201    30
##  dplyr 4.583801 5.173901 6.492414 5.631750 6.400001 19.865601    30
m2 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison base v dplyr',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m2)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

# Next time you create an empty vector with c(), try to replace it with vector(type, length)

x <- vector("numeric", 5)
print(x)
## [1] 0 0 0 0 0
f1 <- function (n){
  x <- c()
  for (i in seq(n)) {
    x <- c(x, i)
  }
  # print(x)
}
f2 <- function (n){
  x <- vector("integer", n)
  for (i in seq(n)) {
    x[i] <- i
  }
  # print(x)
}
m3 <- microbenchmark(
  nosize = f1(1e5),
  size = f2(1e5),
  times = 5
)
print(m3)
## Unit: milliseconds
##    expr        min           lq         mean       median           uq
##  nosize 15206.5563 15249.521201 16410.668501 15345.500301 16822.944901
##    size     3.1976     3.849901     6.583001     7.501201     7.791501
##         max neval
##  19428.8198     5
##     10.5748     5
m3 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison vector size v no size',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m3)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

v1 <- function(dt){
  d <- mean(dt[dt$b > .5, ]$a)
  # print(d)
}
v2 <- function(dt){
  d <- mean(dt$a[dt$b > .5])
  # print(d)
}
m5 <- microbenchmark(
  row_operation = v1(dt),
  column_operation = v2(dt),
  times = 10
)
print(m5)
## Unit: microseconds
##              expr     min      lq     mean   median      uq      max neval
##     row_operation 527.301 542.501 857.8308 570.6505 630.701 3378.201    10
##  column_operation 144.301 153.501 481.1008 162.6505 171.801 3302.100    10
m5 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison column v row',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m5)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

num <- 1e7
s1 <- function(num){
  d <- 1
  for(i in 1:num){
    d <- d * i
  }
  return(d)
}
s2 <- function(num){
  d <- 1
  for(i in seq(num)){
    d <- d * i
  }
  return(d)
}
m6<-microbenchmark(
  noseq = s1(num),
  seq = s2(num),
  times = 20
)
print(m6)
## Unit: milliseconds
##   expr     min       lq     mean   median       uq      max neval
##  noseq 201.309 202.1258 208.8474 205.9202 212.3191 247.5144    20
##    seq 228.163 230.2016 236.7001 232.4170 239.7089 273.6209    20
m6 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison seq v no seq',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m6)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

# New pipe

set.seed(123)
demo <- data.frame(
  x = rnorm(10^6),
  y = rnorm(10^6),
  z = rnorm(10^6)
)
# Microbenchmarking native pipe vs dplyr pipe
m7 <- microbenchmark(
  native_pipe = {
    demo |>
      filter(x > 0) |>
      mutate(new_col = y * 2) |>
      summarise(avg_z = mean(z))
  },
  dplyr_pipe = {
    demo %>%
      filter(x > 0) %>%
      mutate(new_col = y * 2) %>%
      summarise(avg_z = mean(z))
  },
  times = 100
)
print(m7)
## Unit: milliseconds
##         expr     min      lq     mean   median      uq      max neval
##  native_pipe 23.6421 26.1354 33.78244 27.50815 29.7543  98.2310   100
##   dplyr_pipe 23.2349 26.6909 34.74483 28.41010 30.2112 103.3664   100
m7 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison new v old pipe',
     ylab = glue('Time {calcpecentage(m7)}'), xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

datatable <- function(df){
  df[, date_updated := as.POSIXct(date_updated, format = "%a %b %d %H:%M:%S %z %Y", tz = "UTC")]
  return(df)
}
dply <- function(df){
  df <- df |> mutate(date_added = as.POSIXct(date_added, format = "%a %b %d %H:%M:%S %z %Y", tz = "UTC"))
  return(df)
}
dtplyr <- function(df){
  df <- df |>
    lazy_dt() |>
    mutate(date_added = as.POSIXct(date_added, format = "%a %b %d %H:%M:%S %z %Y", tz = "UTC")) |>
    as.data.table()
  return(df)
}
m8<-microbenchmark(
  datatable = datatable(df),
  dply = dply(df),
  dtplyr = dtplyr(df),
  times = 10
)
print(m8)
## Unit: microseconds
##       expr       min          lq    mean       median          uq     max neval
##  datatable     293.2     302.701  661657     427.9005     472.401 6610771    10
##       dply 6671084.6 6703032.001 6852443 6833368.0000 6955288.000 7147347    10
##     dtplyr 6700470.4 6820957.901 7047028 6965280.1010 7241438.601 7620665    10
m8 |>
boxplot(horizontal = TRUE, main = 'Time comparison',
     ylab = 'Time', xlab = 'Type function',
     cex.main = 1.3, cex.lab = 1.3, cex.axis = 1.3)

snappy <- function(dt){
  write_dataset(dt,
                glue("{format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d_%H%M%S_')}snappy_data"),
                format = "parquet", compression="snappy")
}
gzip <- function(dt){
  write_dataset(dt,
                glue("{format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d_%H%M%S_')}gzip_data"),
                format = "parquet", compression="gzip")
}
uncomp <- function(dt){
  write_dataset(dt,
                glue("{format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d_%H%M%S_')}unc_data"),
                format = "parquet", compression="uncompressed")
}
rdsfile <- function(dt){
  saveRDS(dt, 
          glue("{format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d_%H%M%S_')}rds_data.rds"))
}
mycsv <- function(dt){
  write_csv(dt, 
            glue("{format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d_%H%M%S_')}csv_data.csv"))
}
m9<-microbenchmark(
  fsnappy = snappy(df),
  fgzip = gzip(df),
  funcomp = uncomp(df),
  frdsfile = rdsfile(df),
  fmycsv = mycsv(df),
  times = 6
)
print(m9)
